glfw
------------------------------------------
GLFW is a free, Open Source, multi-platform library for OpenGL and OpenGL ES
application development. It provides a simple, platform-independent API for
creating windows and contexts, reading input, handling events, etc.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.6.1-1
  libglfw-devel-3.2.1-1bl1
  libglfw3-3.2.1-1bl1
  libX11-devel-1.6.4-1
  libX11_6-1.6.4-1
  libXcursor-devel-1.1.14-1
  libXcursor1-1.1.14-1
  libXinerama-devel-1.1.3-1
  libXinerama1-1.1.3-1
  libXrandr-devel-1.5.1-1
  libXrandr2-1.5.1-1
  libXxf86vm-devel-1.1.4-1bl1
  libXxf86vm1-1.1.4-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.23.0-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  gcc-objc-5.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/glfw/glfw

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/glfw/glfw/archive/3.2.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack glfw-3.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./glfw-3.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glfw-3.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/glfw-3.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglfw3-3.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglfw-devel-3.2.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(glfw)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/glfw.README
  /usr/share/doc/glfw/COPYING.txt
  /usr/share/doc/glfw/README.md

(libglfw3)
  /usr/bin/cygglfw-3.dll

(libglfw-devel)
  /usr/include/GLFW/glfw3.h
  /usr/include/GLFW/glfw3native.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw3/glfw3Config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw3/glfw3ConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw3/glfw3Targets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw3/glfw3Targets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libglfw.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/glfw3.pc

